source: plasm-oss/crates/plasm-core/src/prompt_render.rs
expression: prompt
---
# Follow the grammar and the teaching TSV below; reply with one valid plasm_program:
#
# Output:
# - Emit only code: either one `plasm_expr`, or one multi-line `plasm_program` with bindings then final roots.
# - Do not emit prose, JSON wrappers, `return`, Markdown fences, or table rows.
# - Prefer bind → narrow/project/transform → few final roots when more than one step is needed.
#
# TSV table semantics:
# - Header is exactly `plasm_expr<TAB>Meaning`; every following row has exactly one tab delimiter.
# - Left cell is either executable syntax or metadata. Right cell is selection guidance only; never copy `Meaning` into output.
# - Executable rows start with an entity surface (`e#`/`Entity`). Copy their left-cell shape, then replace placeholders.
# - Metadata rows whose left cell is only `v#`/`value domain` define reusable value types. Metadata rows whose left cell is only `p#`/`field` define keyed slots. Metadata rows are never executable roots.
# - `Meaning` fragments joined by ` · ` stay inside `Meaning`; they are not operators.
#
# Symbol and fill rules:
# - `e#` = entity surface; `m#` = method/action surface; `p#` = keyed field/parameter/relation slot; `v#` = value-domain metadata only.
# - Entity-ref slots in `Meaning` look like `ref:Zone · str · Zone identifier`: canonical entity, id wire type, short note — not `plasm_expr` syntax.
# - Never write `v#` inside a `plasm_expr`. Use `p#` keys in code and use `v#` rows only to understand allowed values/types.
# - `$` appears only in taught examples as a required fill placeholder. Replace every `$`; never emit `$`.
# - `<id>`, `<value>`, `<receiver>`, and `elem` in this contract are meta-variables, not syntax tokens.
# - If a copied row contains `..`, it is an ellipsis for omitted optional keys. Remove `..` or replace it with additional `p#=<value>` assignments before final output.
# - If `Meaning` says `optional params: pA, pB`, those keys may be added only as keyed assignments with real values.
# - Projection rows ending `[p#,…]` teach a valid field set. Reuse that suffix only on another expression returning the same entity or list type.
# - Relation rows end with `.p#`/`.field`; apply them to any executable receiver row for that same entity type.
# - `page(sN_pgM)` uses a continuation handle returned by a prior response; copy the handle exactly and optionally add `, limit=N`.
#
# Grammar:
# plasm_program ::= plasm_expr | binding+ roots
# binding       ::= ident "=" node
# roots         ::= root ("," root)*
# root          ::= ident | plasm_expr
# node          ::= (plasm_expr | ident) postfix* row_template? | ident "=>" value_or_template
# plasm_expr    ::= entity_expr [projection] | page
# entity_expr   ::= query_all | get | query | relation | method | create_action | search
# query_all     ::= e#
# get           ::= e#(<id>) or e#(p#=<value>, p#=<value>)
# query         ::= e#{p#=<value>, …}
# relation      ::= <receiver>.p#
# method        ::= e#(<id>).m#() or e#(<id>).m#(p#=<value>, …)
# create_action ::= e#.m#(p#=<value>, …)
# search        ::= e#~"text"
# page          ::= page(sN_pgM) | page(sN_pgM, limit=N)
# projection    ::= e#(<id>)[p#,…] | "[" fields "]"
# postfix       ::= ".limit(N)" | ".page_size(N)" | ".sort(field[, dir])" | ".aggregate(specs)" | ".group_by(field, specs)" | ".singleton()" | "[" fields "]"
# row_template  ::= ("[" fields "]")? "<<TAG" template_body "TAG"
# fields        ::= [p#,…]
# specs         ::= name=count | name=sum(field) | name=avg(field) | name=min(field) | name=max(field) [, ...]
# dir           ::= desc | asc | descending | ascending
# value_or_template ::= literal | ident | ident.field | _.field | [elem, ...] | heredoc
# literal       ::= quoted string | number | bool | null
#
# Composition rules:
# - Multi-line program strings use literal newlines: one binding per line, final roots last. Spaces never separate statements.
# - Postfix transforms and `[fields]` may chain on any bound node or expression that returns rows.
# - To turn rows into text, bind a template block: `report = rows[p#,…] <<TAG` newline template newline `TAG`, or `report = rows <<TAG` when columns can be inferred.
# - Template blocks use Minijinja with `rows` as the input array. The bound result is a row with a `content` field; pass `report.content` to string/body parameters or `=>` payloads.
# - Do not use `report.content` as a final root or relation receiver. Return `report` if you want the generated text row; continue relations only from row-producing query/relation/projection bindings.
# - Heredoc opener `<<TAG` is followed by newline; the first later line whose trimmed text is `TAG` closes it. Choose a tag not present in the body.
# - Examples: scoped child list `e#{p#=e#(<id>)}`; array argument `p#=[e#(<id>), …]`. Quoted strings use only `\"` and `\\` escapes.
# - `markdown`/`html`/`document`/`json_text`/`blob` values (per `Meaning`): `<<TAG` … `TAG` only; e.g. `m#(..., p#=<<TXT` + newline body + `TXT` newline `)`.
#

